  <div id="poddiscbox" class="poddisc1">
    <h3>Knifepoint Horror is well-known within the genre for quality, creepy content. Each episode is narrated by a small cast, usually only one actor, but they occasionally branch out to a 4-6 person performance. Well-crafted, but the background ambiance can sometimes be overpowering.</h3><h3>Production Status: Ongoing.</h3>
  </div>
  <div id="poddiscbox2" class="poddisc2">
    <h3>Initially started as a Reddit forum back in 2010, The NoSleep Podcast has grown into a thriving, submission-based horror podcast. The show often features a few shorter stories within each episode, making it ideal for people with short breaks or attention spans. In addition to hosting authors who have gone on to publish their work, the podcast has also featured some celebrity guests such as Kate Siegel (The Haunting of Hill House, Midnight Mass) and Elijah Wood (The Lord of the Rings series, Happy Feet).</h3><h3>Production Status: Ongoing.</h3>
  </div>
  <div id="poddiscbox3" class="poddisc3">
    <h3>Lore is a non-fiction podcast that examines history and human behavior through the lens of folklore and fairytales; Lore has been a critical darling since its premiere in 2015 and has spawned not only a series of books but also an Amazon TV series which ran for two seasons; creator Aaron Mahnke hosts every episode of the podcast and the show.</h3><h3>Production Status: Ongoing.<h3>
  </div>
